A lot of older Millennial women seem to have genuinely enjoyed the concept of tattoos and found it fun getting elaborate "artistic" ones, but young women now are basically treating them as self-harm scars, e.g. they will have a new one done after breaking up with their boyfriend.

It used to be a symbol of transgression and rebellion sure to make your parents mad, but now that society is fully desensitized to it, it's turned to the same thing as people administering electric shocks to themselves out of boredom when forced to sit in an empty room for hours.

Dull pain and being shocked (even literally) are still preferable to feeling nothing. It's why these women are also often attracted to horror movies of the particularly gruesome sort. You need to wake up. Adrenalin is preferable to acetylcholine. Cold shower with few extra steps.

Dzhonrid actually married Stalin's daughter. Complicated stuff. There is currently a "DzhonridÂ  Abdurashitov" in Moscow who publishes esoteric physics stuff like "Study of the Compton Scattering of Entangled Annihilation Photons", no idea what his relation is with the above is.
